  "Eternal_Life": {
    "name": "Eternal Life",
    "implicits": [
      "- #% of Damage taken bypasses Energy Shield: The damage you would have taken to life that bypasses energy shield is ignored until energy shield is fully depleted, effectively granting an equivalent less damage taken modifier. For example, if 20% of damage bypassed energy shield, you would take 20% less damage until energy shield is fully depleted. If a single hit deals enough damage to fully deplete energy shield, the remainder of the damage is fully taken to life.",
      "- Life loss: As long as the player has energy shield, effects that cause you to lose life are ignored, such as [Event Horizon](Event_Horizon/edit.md \"Event Horizon (page does not exist)\")'s Lose 3% of maximum Life and Energy Shield when you use a Chaos Skill or ![](../images/thumb/a/a3/Death_Articulated_inventory_icon.png/16px-Death_Articulated_inventory_icon.png)[Death Articulated](Death_Articulated.md \"Death Articulated\")Death Articulated"
    ],
    "explicits": [
      "+(17-23)% to [Chaos Resistance](Chaos_Resistance.md \"Chaos Resistance\")",
      "- Life recovery: The player is unable to recover life while you have energy shield, such as if you depleted all ES, took damage to life, then recovered some ES[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1). Although this can be used strategically to maintain [low life](Low_life.md \"Low life\") status (e.g. for [Pain Attunement](Pain_Attunement.md \"Pain Attunement\")), it also means there is no way to benefit from life recovery while you have energy shield.",
      "- Life costs: The character is unable to use any skill or effect that requires you to spend life in order to occur, such as using ![](../images/thumb/0/0c/Lifetap_inventory_icon.png/16px-Lifetap_inventory_icon.png)[Lifetap](Lifetap.md \"Lifetap\")Lifetap[Support](Support_%28gem_tag%29.md \"Support (gem tag)\")",
      "- Sacrificing life: It is possible to use effects that [sacrifice](Sacrifice_%28keyword%29.md \"Sacrifice (keyword)\") life, but no life will actually be sacrificed. This causes effects that scale with the amount of sacrificed life, such as ![](../images/thumb/9/94/Demon_Stitcher_inventory_icon.png/16px-Demon_Stitcher_inventory_icon.png)[Demon Stitcher](Demon_Stitcher.md \"Demon Stitcher\")Demon Stitcher",
      "+(80-120) to maximum Life",
      "- ![](../images/thumb/5/57/The_Last_Lament_inventory_icon.png/8px-The_Last_Lament_inventory_icon.png)[The Last Lament](The_Last_Lament.md \"The Last Lament\")The Last Lament"
    ],
    "flavour": ") [\\[1\\]](Passive_Skill:AscendancyWitch3Notable6.md"
  },
